subtests.name: URL: Setting <mailto:me@example.net>.protocol = 'http' Cannot-be-a-base URL doesn’t have a host, but URL in a special scheme must.
URL: Setting <mailto:you@example.net>.username = 'me' Cannot-be-a-base means no username
URL: Setting <mailto:me@example.net>.password = 'secret' Cannot-be-a-base means no password
URL: Setting <mailto:me@example.net>.host = 'example.com' Cannot-be-a-base means no host
URL: Setting <mailto:me@example.net>.hostname = 'example.com' Cannot-be-a-base means no host
URL: Setting <mailto:me@example.net>.pathname = '/foo' Opaque paths cannot be set
